content: This game is a little masterpiece: visual arts and music create a unique atmosphere that teleports you into a different dimension. You don't need photorealism or heavy 3D graphics to create something excellent, coherent and engaging as this little game is. I beg Avokiddo to seriously consider a Thinkrolls Space sequel, by continuing in exactly the same direction and with the same team that developed and designed this marvelous game.

Daughter loves these little guys, and she blazes through these puzzles - amazing. She's only 3. I asked her what she loved best and she says the purple cheeser that eats the cheese. Good mechanics, love the unlockable system of characters and the progress saving/replay options.
replyContent: Thank you so much for the great review! We're so glad to hear that you and your daughter love our app!

content: Great app for problem solving but my 6 year old finished it in a day with very little help.
Best tablet game I've ever played. So fun and simple. My 4 and 6 year old play with me on their tablets on easy mode. No ads. Just really satisfied.
Best think rolls game yet. The kids ( 5 and 7) are enjoying the new puzzle elements.
Was fun for about 2 hours then progress became too difficult because alien's movement became too dependent on the (lack of?) sensitivity of the screen of my 12 month old Samsung S8.
I I have a 5 year old and she loves it
Another great set of puzzles This time set in space!
Super nice app for learning solving logic problems, my 6 years old kid loves it, and mee too!
Another great puzzle game from avokiddo studio. Nice music and design. Puzzles that will excite kids and their parents, too. It is an app that entertains you through mind practicing.
